# /tests/crasher — deliberate-crash fixture for svcmgr's restart path.
#
# Recipe lives under /config/svcmgr/tests/, which svcmgr does NOT scan.
# Co-staged with svctest (services-surface harness) in CI and stageable
# by hand: copy this file into /config/svcmgr/services/ between
# `cargo xtask build` and `cargo xtask run`. See docs/testing.md.
#
# Exercises restart-surface preservation: on every spawn crasher asserts
# its argv / env / cwd / seed match this recipe, logs `[crasher] … ok`,
# then deliberately faults. `restart = always` drives svcmgr to respawn
# it; with MAX_RESTARTS the budget bounds it to a fixed number of spawns,
# then it is left degraded (`critical = no` — the system continues). A
# surface that fails to survive restart makes crasher log `FATAL:`, which
# fails the run. Confined to a read-only `/tests` subtree to model the
# min-privilege shape future real services use.
binary    = /tests/crasher
argv      = crasher selftest
env       = CRASHER_MARKER=107
namespace = subtree:/tests:LOOKUP+READDIR+STAT+READ
cwd       = /tests
restart   = always
critical  = no
seed      = svcmgr pwrmgr.deny
